lexUnit.name: jam.v
lexUnit.definition: FN: squeeze or pack tightly into a space, sometimes with force

sentence.text: Overcome with rage and frustration , Dora jammed a fist against her mouth and gnawed at her knuckles .
With a groan of defeat he slumped back against the reception desk , jamming his elbow against the counter .
She dried the udder and pulled the three-legged stool across , jamming the first bucket between her knees as she sat down , so that Florence could not kick it over .
He jammed a finger in each ear .
Hargreave dug out the stub of a cigar from his top pocket and examined it with distaste before jamming it in his mouth .
I jammed one finger in my ear against the fourth circle of hell that had just broken loose .
Chris attempts to clear his desk by jamming all outstanding items in the biggest , bottom drawer .
Outrage turned to agitation when she saw that he was jamming the key in the lock with such force that the flesh on his fingers was turning white .
She laughed hysterically , jamming her fingers into her mouth to muffle the sound .
She jammed her fists into her pockets .
Claire jams the black box into her shoulder bag .
I smiled at her , and she jammed a copy of Pravda into my hand , her smile still ticking over .
Donald jammed the shotgun into the crook of bone under Nathan 's jaw .
He stopped , jammed his hands on his hips and leaned forward from the waist in a belligerent posture .
He jammed the one-eyed spectacles onto his face and fled .
The tyres screamed as he jammed his foot to the floor and the car shot into traffic .
He jammed the point firmly under the great fish 's jaw bone and used the other curve of S as a carrying handle .
He slid the ramrod out , jammed it down the long barrel , then pulled it free .
He put the cheese in the fridge and jammed a stool up against the door ; otherwise it would swing open , and everything would go bad .
The younger of the trio looked at McCann and Morton and decided he would be better advised not to try and reach the .38 he had jammed into his belt .
The table was strewn with books and papers and candle-ends jammed into empty bottles , and the floor was similarly littered , but with boots and boxes .
The silencer jammed into the muzzle of the .45 made the weapon look enormous .
The estate-car reeled drunkenly , shot sideways across the road and oncoming traffic , and came to rest with its bonnet jammed in the sloping grass bank edging the road on the other side .
Trent almost laughed with relief as he imagined the six-foot-four Customs officer at the wheel , empty pipe jammed between his teeth .
A BLIND man fought off a bull terrier that attacked his guide dog -- by jamming his fist down its throat and smacking it between the eyes .
Markby hastily jammed dolly 's arm back into its socket .
